properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued February 8 at 2:34PM CST until February 9 at 6:00PM CST by NWS Green Bay WI
properties.description:
...SNOW EXPECTED ON SUNDAY...

.A low pressure system will track from the central Plains toward
southern Wisconsin on Sunday and into Lower Michigan Sunday
evening. Snow will spread across the area from southwest to
northeast during the morning, continue through afternoon, and then
end during the evening.

* WHAT...Snow expected. Total snow accumulations of 3 to 6
inches.

* WHERE...Langlade County.

* WHEN...From 6 AM to 6 PM CST Sunday.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions. Travel could become
dangerous at times.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS....The heaviest snow is expected from late
morning into early afternoon, which will create much lower
visibility along with slippery road conditions.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY NOW IN EFFECT FROM 6 AM TO 6 PM CST SUNDAY
